films.title: Chunnel
films.overview: There's an explosion in the Chunnel. And the U.S. President's daughter gets stuck in there. There is more than meets the eye in this complex, layered film.
films.tagline: There's a war 100 meters below the English Channel

films.title: Prognosis Negative
films.overview: A doctor mulls over the consequences of a new miracle cure he has created while balancing his need to test it fully. But should he to it on his family?
films.tagline: How far will a man go to find a cure?

films.title: Checkmate
films.overview: Checkmate is about a king who likes chess... and finds himself in real-life jeopardy when, like in the game, everyone is after the king. According to transcripts, this FANTASTIC dialogue exchange happens in the movie: Man: I didn't know you enjoyed chess, your majesty. King: Why wouldn't I? Man: Because the king is always in jeopardy. King: Yes, but it's only a game. Man: (suspiciously) Yes, of course. Only a game.
films.tagline: Being the king is not a game... or is it?

films.title: Death Blow
films.overview: When someone tries to blow you up, not because of who you are, but for different reasons altogether.  Set in the 80's, Adam is an amnesia patient who has government secrets hidden, but he can't remember where. John Rock is the only one who can protect him from the Soviets while the good guys try to get Adam to remember where the secrets are hidden. Will they be able to keep him alive long enough to find them? Quick! Time is running out.

films.title: Blimp
films.overview: Oh, the humanity! Based on the true story of the Hindenberg, this docu-drama follows the interactions between five passengers on the ill-fated ... well ... blimp on its maiden voyage.

films.title: Sack Lunch
films.overview: An unpretentious, lighthearted alternative to the gravitas-filled films of the day. Your brain deserves a break today. Shift into neutral, grab a snack and melt into your seat as you get lost in this fun little comedy.
